Note:
This file handles compiler driver orchestration and compilation process coordination.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process compilation orchestration and compiler phase coordination
- Handle compilation pipeline management and compilation process control
- Manage compilation optimization and compilation performance utilities
- Process compilation validation and compilation process monitoring

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Compiler driver orchestration is fundamental to compiler operation and compilation process
- Proper driver handling ensures efficient compilation pipeline and process coordination
- Driver utilities support compilation phases, pipeline management, and compilation optimization

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Compilation orchestration and compiler phase coordination
- Compilation pipeline management and compilation process control
- Compilation optimization and compilation performance utilities
- Compilation validation and compilation process monitoring
:End Note

Note: Hybrid Compiler Driver for v0.0.8.5
Note: This driver uses v0.0.8.4.5 lexer/parser with v0.0.8.5 codegen primitives
Note: This is a temporary solution to test our codegen migration

Note: Per P1-E v3 Layer 3: import the compile orchestrator that owns
Note: the per-file AST -> HIR -> MIR -> optimize_program -> LIR ->
Note: codegen pipeline. The compile_program call at line 220 resolves
Note: through this import.
Import "compiler/driver/compile_orchestrator.runa" as CompileOrchestrator
Note: Frontend providers — imported so the driver's bare calls to lexer_create/
Note: parser_create/program_add_* resolve to the modules' module-qualified
Note: symbols (lexical_lexer__*, parsing_parser__*, parsing_program__*) at link
Note: time, exactly as the compile_program call resolves through CompileOrchestrator.
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/lexer_factory.runa" as LexerFactory
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/program.runa" as Program
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Note: string_index_of / string_substring back the platform-leaf skip predicate
Note: (_import_is_platform_skipped) below; they live in string_primitive, not
Note: string_core, and are otherwise unused by the bare driver code.
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrimitive
Note: AST + List providers — process_imports operates on the AST_PROGRAM node
Note: returned by parser_parse_program (top-level declarations live in the
Note: children List at AST offset 24), so the driver's bare calls to the AST node
Note: accessors (ast_node_get_*) and the List primitives (get/size/append/create)
Note: resolve to the modules' module-qualified symbols at link time.
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa" as AST
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: Process to read entire file contents into memory
Process called "read_file_internal" takes filename as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read entire file using runtime function (handles file open failure internally)
    Let content be runtime_read_file(filename)

    Note: Check if reading failed (equivalent to fopen() returning NULL)
    If content is equal to 0:
        Note: Alert error message (equivalent to fprintf(stderr, "[MAIN ERROR] Could not open input file '%s'\n", filename))
        Let error_msg_temp be string_concat("[MAIN ERROR] Could not open input file '", filename)
        Let error_msg be string_concat(error_msg_temp, "'")
        deallocate(error_msg_temp)
        Alert error_msg
        deallocate(error_msg)
        Return 0
    End If

    Return content
End Process

Note: AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT discriminant as emitted by build_import_statement
Note: (compiler/frontend/parsing/ast_builder.runa). The import path string is
Note: stored in the node's value slot (AST offset 40) and the optional alias is a
Note: child identifier; the path is therefore read with ast_node_get_value.
Constant DRIVER_AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT as Integer is 2016

Note: AST discriminants the sep-comp mangle-resolve pass keys on. These mirror the
Note: canonical constants in compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa (AST_IDENTIFIER 1001,
Note: AST_CALL_EXPRESSION 1005, AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION 3000); declared locally here so
Note: the driver's pass reads them without a cross-module Constant reference.
Constant DRIVER_AST_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 1001
Constant DRIVER_AST_CALL_EXPRESSION as Integer is 1005
Constant DRIVER_AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION as Integer is 3000

Note:
==============================================================================
TARGET-ONLY PLATFORM-LEAF INCLUSION (universal stage2 duplicate-symbol fix)
==============================================================================

The assembly aggregator modules (compiler/frontend/primitives/assembly/{register_map,
syscall,atomic,threading,machine_code}.runa) each Import EVERY one of the 18
canonical platform leaves -- e.g. register_map.runa imports
primitives/platform/<key>/registers.runa for all of linux_x86_64, linux_arm64,
mips32, riscv64, darwin_*, windows_*, ... Every leaf defines the SAME bare global
names (REG_SP, get_param_register, get_return_register, atomic_*, memory_barrier_*,
...) but with DIFFERENT per-platform values (REG_SP = "rsp" on linux_x86_64 vs
"sp" on linux_arm64; get_param_register returns a different register set per ISA).

When process_imports_into merges any import-bearing file's closure, all 18 leaves
get spliced into the root program, so the emitted assembly defines each of those
~131 symbols 2-18 times and `as --64` fails with ~506 "symbol already defined"
errors -- no module can produce a linkable object. Because the symbols are NOT
byte-identical across platforms, COMDAT/weak coalescing would be a correctness
bug (it would pick one platform's value arbitrarily). The only correct fix is
TARGET-ONLY INCLUSION: when a --target platform key is set, skip importing any
primitives/platform/<other_key>/ leaf, keeping only the target platform's set.

This mirrors the monolith's import_system.runa::_import_is_platform_skipped
(v0.0.8.4.5.3.5/src/import_system.runa ~143-230). DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY is
the driver-local copy of the validated --target key, published by main alongside
the orchestrator's set_active_target_platform_key. When 0 (no --target), no skip
occurs and the legacy all-platform-merge behavior is preserved exactly (the
runtime platform-dispatch ladders then select at run time).
:End Note
Let DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY be 0

Process called "set_driver_target_platform_key" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Publish the validated --target key string to the import-skip predicate.
    Note: The key is a get_command_line_arg result (freed only at process exit), so
    Note: it outlives the whole compile, matching the monolith's lifetime contract.
    Set DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY to key
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "_driver_is_platform_key" takes seg as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Return 1 if seg is one of the 18 canonical platform-directory keys, 0 otherwise.
    The key set is the directory names under primitives/platform/. A miss here
    (e.g. the segment "platform_selector.runa") means the import is NOT a
    platform-specific leaf and is never skipped. seg is a NUL-terminated string.
    :End Note
    If seg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "linux_x86_64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "linux_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "linux_arm32") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "mips32") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "mips64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "darwin_x86_64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "darwin_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "freebsd_x64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "freebsd_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "netbsd_x64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "netbsd_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "openbsd_x64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "openbsd_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "windows_x86_64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "windows_arm64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "powerpc") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "riscv32") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If string_equals(seg, "riscv64") is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "_import_is_platform_skipped" takes import_filename as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Return 1 = skip this import entirely (foreign platform leaf), 0 = process it.
    A skip happens only when ALL of the following hold:
      - DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY is set (non-zero),
      - the path contains the substring "primitives/platform/",
      - the segment immediately after "primitives/platform/" (up to the next '/')
        is one of the 18 canonical platform keys,
      - that segment is not equal to DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY.
    platform_selector.runa survives: its segment is "platform_selector.runa", which
    _driver_is_platform_key rejects, so it is never skipped.
    :End Note
    If DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If import_filename is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Locate the "primitives/platform/" marker within the import path.
    Let marker_pos be string_index_of(import_filename, "primitives/platform/")
    If marker_pos is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: The platform key starts immediately after the 20-char marker.
    Let seg_start be marker_pos plus 20
    Let path_len be string_length(import_filename)
    If seg_start is greater than or equal to path_len:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan forward from seg_start to the first '/' (ASCII 47). seg_end indexes
    Note: the delimiting slash or path_len when the segment is the bare trailing
    Note: component. string_substring takes (str, start, length), so the segment
    Note: length is seg_end minus seg_start.
    Let seg_end be seg_start
    Let seg_done be 0
    While seg_done is equal to 0:
        If seg_end is greater than or equal to path_len:
            Set seg_done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let scan_ch be string_char_at(import_filename, seg_end)
            If scan_ch is equal to 47:
                Set seg_done to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set seg_end to seg_end plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Let segment_length be seg_end minus seg_start
    If segment_length is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let segment be string_substring(import_filename, seg_start, segment_length)
    If segment is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: A non-key segment (e.g. "platform_selector.runa") is never skipped.
    If _driver_is_platform_key(segment) is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Known key. Skip iff it is a different platform from the target.
    If string_equals(segment, DRIVER_TARGET_PLATFORM_KEY) is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Process imports: load, parse, and merge imported modules' declarations
Note: into the importing program's top-level declaration list.
Note: .
Note: parser_parse_program returns an AST_PROGRAM node (discriminant 3500) whose
Note: top-level declarations -- imports, constants, processes, types -- all live
Note: in the children List at AST offset 24 (count at offset 32). An imported
Note: module's Constants must therefore be appended to the importing program's
Note: children List so lower_program lowers them as siblings: lower_constant_statement
Note: interns each imported Constant and records its literal value on the symbol's
Note: const slots, and lower_identifier then inlines a bare reference (e.g.
Note: TOKEN_LET) to that value. Merging only functions/types -- and via the wrong
Note: (Program-record) offsets at that -- left imported Constants invisible, so a
Note: bare reference resolved to symbol id 0 and silently dropped the enclosing
Note: function. Appending ALL children fixes constants, functions, and types
Note: uniformly through the single mechanism lower_program already consumes.
Note: .
Note: visited holds the resolved path of every module already merged so a diamond
Note: or cyclic import graph merges each module exactly once (no duplicate symbols,
Note: no infinite recursion). Returns 0 on success, 1 on failure.
Process called "process_imports" takes program as Integer, input_filename as Integer returns Integer:
    Let visited be list_create()
    Note: insert_pos threads the front-insertion cursor through the recursion so
    Note: imported declarations land BEFORE the importing module's own declarations
    Note: (a constant must be interned before the function that references it lowers;
    Note: lower_program's forward-declaration pre-pass covers processes only, not
    Note: Constants). A return value < 0 signals a fatal import error.
    Note: Seed the ROOT file's own import-path key into visited so a cyclic import
    Note: back to the root (e.g. expression_parsers.runa imports parser.runa which
    Note: imports expression_parsers.runa) is recognized as already-merged and the
    Note: root's own declarations are NOT spliced into itself a second time. The
    Note: seed MUST use the SAME literal-relative form the cyclic importer writes in
    Note: its Import statement, because import_already_visited compares raw strings
    Note: against import_filename = ast_node_get_value(child), the verbatim Import
    Note: path string. argv[1] is supplied to the compiler in that same project-root-
    Note: relative form (e.g. "compiler/frontend/parsing/expression_parsers.runa"),
    Note: so the seed and the back-edge literal are byte-identical and the existing
    Note: string_equals compare matches without any path canonicalization.
    If input_filename is not equal to 0:
        list_append(visited, input_filename)
    End If

    Note: Sep-comp stage 3a (root seed): stamp the ROOT program's OWN Process
    Note: definitions with the root file path (input_filename = argv[1]) BEFORE the
    Note: merge runs. The merge appends imported decls (each carrying its own
    Note: import_filename via process_def_set_source_file) AFTER these, so root-origin
    Note: definitions are tagged here exactly once and the splice loop never
    Note: re-stamps them. process_def_set_source_file guards on the discriminant so
    Note: only AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION nodes are touched. When input_filename is 0
    Note: (no path supplied) the root defs stay unstamped and fall through to the
    Note: no-mangle path in the resolve pass, preserving the plain-name build.
    If input_filename is not equal to 0:
        Let root_own_children be ast_node_get_children(program)
        If root_own_children is not equal to 0:
            Let root_own_count be list_length(root_own_children)
            Let ri be 0
            While ri is less than root_own_count:
                Let root_decl be list_get(root_own_children, ri)
                If root_decl is not equal to 0:
                    process_def_set_source_file(root_decl, input_filename)
                End If
                Set ri to ri plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let result be process_imports_into(program, program, visited, 0)
    If result is less than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Recursive worker. root is the AST_PROGRAM whose children list accumulates
Note: every merged declaration; current is the AST_PROGRAM whose imports are being
Note: processed this level (root on the first call). visited records merged paths.
Note: insert_pos is the index in root's children List at which the next imported
Note: declaration is inserted. Returns the updated insert_pos on success, or -1 on
Note: a fatal import error.
Process called "process_imports_into" takes root as Integer, current as Integer, visited as Integer, insert_pos as Integer returns Integer:
    If current is equal to 0:
        Return insert_pos
    End If

    Note: Top-level declarations of `current` are its AST children (offset 24).
    Let children be ast_node_get_children(current)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return insert_pos
    End If
    Let child_count be list_length(children)

    Note: The root's children List receives every merged declaration; on recursion
    Note: the imported module's declarations are inserted into the original root so
    Note: they become siblings of the importing program's own top-level declarations.
    Let root_children be ast_node_get_children(root)
    If root_children is equal to 0:
        Return insert_pos
    End If

    Let cursor be insert_pos
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be list_get(children, i)
        If child is not equal to 0:
            Let child_kind be ast_node_get_type(child)
            If child_kind is equal to DRIVER_AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT:
                Note: Import path is the raw string stored in the node value slot.
                Let import_filename be ast_node_get_value(child)
                If import_filename is equal to 0:
                    Alert "[IMPORT ERROR] Import statement has no path"
                    Return -1
                End If

                Note: Target-only platform-leaf inclusion. When a --target key is
                Note: set, a primitives/platform/<other_key>/... import belongs to a
                Note: foreign platform whose bare globals (REG_*, get_param_register,
                Note: atomic_*, ...) collide with the target leaf's at assembly time.
                Note: Skip it before any read/tokenize/parse/merge so only the target
                Note: platform's leaves reach codegen. Mirrors the monolith's
                Note: _import_is_platform_skipped gate in process_imports_recursive.
                If _import_is_platform_skipped(import_filename) is equal to 1:
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    Continue
                End If

                Note: Merge each module exactly once.
                Let already be import_already_visited(visited, import_filename)
                If already is equal to 0:
                    list_append(visited, import_filename)

                    Let import_source be read_file_internal(import_filename)
                    If import_source is equal to 0:
                        Let read_err_msg be string_concat("[IMPORT ERROR] Failed to read import file: ", import_filename)
                        Alert read_err_msg
                        deallocate(read_err_msg)
                        Return -1
                    End If

                    Note: Modular frontend pipeline: tokenize then parse the
                    Note: imported source. The modular parser_create takes
                    Note: (token_stream, arena); the legacy one-arg form is gone.
                    Let import_source_length be string_length(import_source)
                    Let import_token_stream be quick_tokenize_string(import_source, import_source_length)
                    If import_token_stream is equal to 0:
                        Let tok_err_msg be string_concat("[IMPORT ERROR] Failed to tokenize import file: ", import_filename)
                        Alert tok_err_msg
                        deallocate(tok_err_msg)
                        deallocate(import_source)
                        Return -1
                    End If

                    Let import_arena be arena_create(65536)
                    Let import_parser be parser_create(import_token_stream, import_arena)
                    Let import_program be parser_parse_program(import_parser)

                    If import_program is equal to 0:
                        Let parse_err_msg be string_concat("[IMPORT ERROR] Failed to parse import file: ", import_filename)
                        Alert parse_err_msg
                        deallocate(parse_err_msg)
                        parser_destroy(import_parser)
                        deallocate(import_source)
                        Return -1
                    End If

                    Note: Transitively merge the imported module's OWN imports
                    Note: first (depth-first) so a constant defined two modules
                    Note: deep is interned before this module's declarations, which
                    Note: are in turn interned before the importing program's.
                    Let nested_cursor be process_imports_into(root, import_program, visited, cursor)
                    If nested_cursor is less than 0:
                        parser_destroy(import_parser)
                        deallocate(import_source)
                        Return -1
                    End If
                    Set cursor to nested_cursor

                    Note: Insert every top-level declaration of the imported module
                    Note: (constants, functions, types) into the root children list at
                    Note: the running cursor so imported declarations precede the
                    Note: importing module's own; skip nested Import statements (already
                    Note: processed above).
                    Let import_children be ast_node_get_children(import_program)
                    If import_children is not equal to 0:
                        Let import_child_count be list_length(import_children)
                        Let m be 0
                        While m is less than import_child_count:
                            Let imported_decl be list_get(import_children, m)
                            If imported_decl is not equal to 0:
                                Let imported_kind be ast_node_get_type(imported_decl)
                                If imported_kind is not equal to DRIVER_AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT:
                                    Note: Sep-comp stage 3a: stamp each spliced Process definition with
                                    Note: its TRUE origin file (import_filename), the verbatim Import path
                                    Note: string for THIS module. The AST mangle-resolve pass later derives
                                    Note: the definition's module key from this exact string, and the
                                    Note: matching call sites derive theirs from the same string, so def
                                    Note: label and call symbol agree by construction. process_def_set_source_file
                                    Note: guards on the AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION discriminant, so non-Process
                                    Note: decls (types, constants, async defs) are left untouched.
                                    process_def_set_source_file(imported_decl, import_filename)
                                    Note: Sep-comp Stage 5: mark this declaration as IMPORTED so the
                                    Note: HIR program-lowering loop skips emitting its body. The decl
                                    Note: stays in the merged AST (spliced below) so the pre-lowering
                                    Note: mangle-resolve pass still sees it as part of the function table
                                    Note: and can resolve cross-module calls to its @PLT symbol; only the
                                    Note: BODY emission is suppressed, so each object contains only its own
                                    Note: module's function definitions (the spliced-in imports become
                                    Note: @PLT externals resolved at final link). process_def_set_imported
                                    Note: guards on the AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION discriminant, so non-Process
                                    Note: decls (types, constants, async defs) are left untouched — types and
                                    Note: constants must still be emitted/interned for the importing module.
                                    process_def_set_imported(imported_decl, 1)
                                    list_insert(root_children, cursor, imported_decl)
                                    Set cursor to cursor plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set m to m plus 1
                        End While
                    End If

                    Note: The merged AST nodes are now owned by the root program.
                    Note: parser_destroy recursively destroys the parser's ast_root
                    Note: tree (destroy_ast_node), which would FREE the very declaration
                    Note: nodes just spliced into root_children -- lower_program would
                    Note: then read freed memory and silently drop the using function.
                    Note: Null the import parser's ast_root (offset 40) first so
                    Note: parser_destroy releases only its own bookkeeping (errors list,
                    Note: context stack, token stream) and leaves the shared AST intact.
                    Note: The import source buffer is retained: identifier name strings
                    Note: referenced by the merged nodes are heap-owned by the lexer and
                    Note: survive, but string-literal token values may alias the source,
                    Note: so the source stays alive for the remainder of the compile.
                    memory_set_qword(import_parser, 40, 0)
                    parser_destroy(import_parser)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Refresh the root program's child_count (offset 32) to reflect every
    Note: declaration inserted so lower_program iterates them all.
    Let new_root_count be list_length(root_children)
    memory_set_qword(root, 32, new_root_count)

    Return cursor
End Process

Note: Linear scan of the visited-path list for an already-merged module path.
Note: Returns 1 if path is present, 0 otherwise.
Process called "import_already_visited" takes visited as Integer, path as Integer returns Integer:
    If visited is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be list_length(visited)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let seen be list_get(visited, i)
        If seen is not equal to 0:
            Let same be string_equals(seen, path)
            If same is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Separate-compilation AST mangle-resolve pass (sep-comp port stages 3c + 4)
Note: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: Runs over the imports-merged AST_PROGRAM after process_imports and before HIR
Note: lowering. The modular backend carries no program/import table and source_file
Note: is severed across HIR/MIR/LIR, so resolution cannot be done at emit time the
Note: way the monolith does it (codegen.runa:4317-4564). Instead this pass uses the
Note: merged AST as the function table: the root's Import statements are the
Note: alias->filename map, each Process definition's stamped source_file (offset 136)
Note: is its origin, and each call's source-level `from Module` alias lives on the
Note: callee identifier's metadata slot (offset 56, written by parse_proc_call_expression).
Note: For every call it finds the target definition, derives the target's module key
Note: from the target's source_file (identical derivation to the def-label path, so
Note: caller symbol and callee label agree), and writes the resolved mangled symbol +
Note: @PLT cross-object flag onto the call node (offsets 104/112) for the HIR->MIR->LIR
Note: carrier chain to thread down to emit_call.
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Derive an identifier-safe module key from a source-file path: the parent
Note: directory component + "_" + the basename (extension stripped), with '.' and
Note: '-' normalized to '_'. Ported from codegen_module_key_from_path
Note: (v0.0.8.4.5.3.5/src/codegen.runa:4015-4142). Returns a freshly heap-allocated
Note: NUL-terminated string the caller owns, or 0 when the path is null/empty or the
Note: basename is empty. Example: "compiler/frontend/parsing/expression_parsers.runa"
Note: -> "parsing_expression_parsers".
Process called "sepcomp_module_key_from_path" takes path as Integer returns Integer:
    If path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let path_len be string_length(path)
    If path_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Locate the last and second-to-last path separators (1-based; 0 = none).
    Let last_sep be 0
    Let prev_sep be 0
    Let scan_i be 0
    While scan_i is less than path_len:
        Let ch be memory_get_byte(path, scan_i)
        Let is_sep be 0
        If ch is equal to 47:
            Set is_sep to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 92:
            Set is_sep to 1
        End If
        If is_sep is equal to 1:
            Set prev_sep to last_sep
            Set last_sep to scan_i plus 1
        End If
        Set scan_i to scan_i plus 1
    End While

    Let basename_start be 0
    If last_sep is greater than 0:
        Set basename_start to last_sep
    End If

    Note: Find the basename's extension boundary (last '.' at or after basename_start).
    Let basename_end be path_len
    Let scan_j be basename_start
    Let last_dot be 0
    While scan_j is less than path_len:
        Let ch2 be memory_get_byte(path, scan_j)
        If ch2 is equal to 46:
            Set last_dot to scan_j plus 1
        End If
        Set scan_j to scan_j plus 1
    End While
    If last_dot is greater than 0:
        Set basename_end to last_dot minus 1
    End If

    Let basename_len be basename_end minus basename_start
    If basename_len is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parent directory slice between prev_sep and (last_sep-1).
    Let parent_start be 0
    Let parent_end be 0
    Let parent_len be 0
    If last_sep is greater than 0:
        If prev_sep is greater than 0:
            Set parent_start to prev_sep
            Set parent_end to last_sep minus 2
            If parent_end is greater than or equal to parent_start:
                Set parent_len to parent_end minus parent_start plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set parent_end to last_sep minus 2
            If parent_end is greater than or equal to parent_start:
                Set parent_len to parent_end minus parent_start plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let total_len be basename_len
    If parent_len is greater than 0:
        Set total_len to parent_len plus 1 plus basename_len
    End If

    Let key_buf be allocate(total_len plus 1)
    If key_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let write_idx be 0
    If parent_len is greater than 0:
        Let pi be 0
        While pi is less than parent_len:
            Let psrc be memory_get_byte(path, parent_start plus pi)
            If psrc is equal to 46:
                Set psrc to 95
            End If
            If psrc is equal to 45:
                Set psrc to 95
            End If
            memory_set_byte(key_buf, write_idx, psrc)
            Set write_idx to write_idx plus 1
            Set pi to pi plus 1
        End While
        memory_set_byte(key_buf, write_idx, 95)
        Set write_idx to write_idx plus 1
    End If
    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than basename_len:
        Let bsrc be memory_get_byte(path, basename_start plus bi)
        If bsrc is equal to 46:
            Set bsrc to 95
        End If
        If bsrc is equal to 45:
            Set bsrc to 95
        End If
        memory_set_byte(key_buf, write_idx, bsrc)
        Set write_idx to write_idx plus 1
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    memory_set_byte(key_buf, write_idx, 0)

    Return key_buf
End Process

Note: Read the plain function-name string of an AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION node. name@80
Note: is the NAME NODE (an AST_IDENTIFIER built by parse_process_name); the actual
Note: name string is its value slot (ast_node_get_value, offset 40). Returns the
Note: name string pointer or 0.
Process called "sepcomp_process_def_name" takes def_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If def_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_node be memory_get_qword(def_node, 80)
    If name_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return ast_node_get_value(name_node)
End Process

Note: Walk the root program's top-level Let statements for the per-unit no-mangle
Note: opt-out sentinel `Let __runa_no_mangle__ be 1`. Files that emit bare cross-file
Note: calls without Import statements (the runtime ABI bridge runtime_api.runa,
Note: program.runa) declare this so neither their definitions nor their calls are
Note: mangled, keeping plain-symbol linkage. Mirrors codegen_is_mangling_disabled
Note: (v0.0.8.4.5.3.5/src/codegen.runa:4212-4236). A top-level Let is an
Note: AST_DEFINE_STATEMENT (2000) whose target identifier name is in the node value
Note: slot. Returns 1 when the sentinel is present, 0 otherwise.
Process called "sepcomp_mangling_disabled" takes root as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be ast_node_get_children(root)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be list_length(children)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let decl be list_get(children, i)
        If decl is not equal to 0:
            Let kind be ast_node_get_type(decl)
            If kind is equal to 2000:
                Let target_name be ast_node_get_value(decl)
                If target_name is not equal to 0:
                    If string_equals(target_name, "__runa_no_mangle__") is equal to 1:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Map a source-level Import alias to the import's filename string (the verbatim
Note: path the merge stamped onto each definition's source_file). The root's Import
Note: statements (AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT, driver kind 2016) store the filename in the
Note: node value slot (offset 40) and the alias as child 0 (an AST_IDENTIFIER whose
Note: value is the alias string). Mirrors codegen_lookup_import_filename_by_alias
Note: (v0.0.8.4.5.3.5/src/codegen.runa:4171-4200). Returns the filename string or 0.
Process called "sepcomp_lookup_import_filename_by_alias" takes root as Integer, alias as Integer returns Integer:
    If alias is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be ast_node_get_children(root)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be list_length(children)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let decl be list_get(children, i)
        If decl is not equal to 0:
            Let kind be ast_node_get_type(decl)
            If kind is equal to DRIVER_AST_IMPORT_STATEMENT:
                Let alias_node be ast_node_get_child(decl, 0)
                If alias_node is not equal to 0:
                    Let alias_name be ast_node_get_value(alias_node)
                    If alias_name is not equal to 0:
                        If string_equals(alias_name, alias) is equal to 1:
                            Return ast_node_get_value(decl)
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Find the AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION among the merged root children whose plain name
Note: matches fn_name AND, when want_key is non-zero, whose source_file's module key
Note: equals want_key (alias-disambiguated lookup). When want_key is 0 the first
Note: name-match wins (bare-call / fallback path). Returns the def node or 0.
Process called "sepcomp_find_target_def" takes root as Integer, fn_name as Integer, want_key as Integer returns Integer:
    If fn_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be ast_node_get_children(root)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be list_length(children)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let decl be list_get(children, i)
        If decl is not equal to 0:
            Let kind be ast_node_get_type(decl)
            If kind is equal to DRIVER_AST_PROCESS_DEFINITION:
                Let decl_name be sepcomp_process_def_name(decl)
                If decl_name is not equal to 0:
                    If string_equals(decl_name, fn_name) is equal to 1:
                        If want_key is equal to 0:
                            Return decl
                        Otherwise:
                            Let decl_src be process_def_get_source_file(decl)
                            If decl_src is not equal to 0:
                                Let decl_key be sepcomp_module_key_from_path(decl_src)
                                If decl_key is not equal to 0:
                                    Let matched be string_equals(decl_key, want_key)
                                    deallocate(decl_key)
                                    If matched is equal to 1:
                                        Return decl
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Compute the module-mangled symbol for a resolved target definition, applying
Note: the monolith's exclusions (codegen_mangled_name_for_func_in,
Note: v0.0.8.4.5.3.5/src/codegen.runa:4246-4295): no mangling for the entry point
Note: `main`, for a definition with no stamped source_file, or when the unit opts out
Note: via __runa_no_mangle__. Returns a freshly heap-allocated "<module_key>__<name>"
Note: string the caller owns, or 0 when no mangling applies (caller then emits the
Note: plain name with a plain call).
Process called "sepcomp_mangle_def" takes target_def as Integer, mangling_disabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If target_def is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mangling_disabled is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fn_name be sepcomp_process_def_name(target_def)
    If fn_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If string_equals(fn_name, "main") is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let source_file be process_def_get_source_file(target_def)
    If source_file is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let module_key be sepcomp_module_key_from_path(source_file)
    If module_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sep_tmp be string_concat(module_key, "__")
    Let full be string_concat(sep_tmp, fn_name)
    deallocate(module_key)
    deallocate(sep_tmp)
    Return full
End Process

Note: Build the module-mangled symbol "<module_key>__<fn_name>" directly from an
Note: already-derived module key and a plain function name. Used for the qualified-
Note: import path where the target module is a SEPARATELY-compiled unit whose defs
Note: are NOT in this compilation's merged AST (e.g. `proc allocate from Layout`
Note: where layout.runa is imported but its bodies were not spliced): the monolith
Note: mangles such a call straight from the import's module key
Note: (codegen_lookup_qualified_target + codegen_module_key_from_path on the import
Note: filename), and the separately-compiled module emits the identical label. Caller
Note: owns the returned heap string. module_key is NOT consumed (caller frees it).
Process called "sepcomp_mangle_with_key" takes module_key as Integer, fn_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If module_key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If fn_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If string_equals(fn_name, "main") is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sep_tmp be string_concat(module_key, "__")
    Let full be string_concat(sep_tmp, fn_name)
    deallocate(sep_tmp)
    Return full
End Process

Note: Resolve and stamp a single AST_CALL_EXPRESSION node. Reads the plain callee
Note: name (callee@80 -> ast_node_get_value) and the optional source-level module
Note: alias (callee identifier metadata @56, written by parse_proc_call_expression).
Note: When the alias names a known Import, the target is looked up alias-disambiguated
Note: by the import's module key; otherwise (bare call or transitively-merged caller
Note: whose alias is unknown here) the first name-match is used. If the resolved
Note: target mangles, the mangled symbol is stored at offset 104 and the @PLT flag at
Note: offset 112; if it does not mangle (main/external/no-source/no-mangle) the call
Note: keeps its plain name and a plain call. Returns 1 always (resolution failure is
Note: not fatal: an unresolved call falls back to the plain-name path that already
Note: worked for non-import bare calls).
Process called "sepcomp_resolve_one_call" takes root as Integer, call_node as Integer, mangling_disabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If call_node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let callee be memory_get_qword(call_node, 80)
    If callee is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let callee_kind be ast_node_get_type(callee)
    If callee_kind is not equal to DRIVER_AST_IDENTIFIER:
        Note: Indirect / computed callee — no static symbol to mangle.
        Return 1
    End If
    Let fn_name be ast_node_get_value(callee)
    If fn_name is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: The source-level `from Module` / `Module.func` alias, if any, was stashed
    Note: on the callee identifier's metadata slot (offset 56) by Stage 2.
    Let alias be memory_get_qword(callee, 56)

    Let want_key be 0
    Let import_filename be 0
    If alias is not equal to 0:
        Set import_filename to sepcomp_lookup_import_filename_by_alias(root, alias)
        If import_filename is not equal to 0:
            Set want_key to sepcomp_module_key_from_path(import_filename)
        End If
    End If

    Let target_def be sepcomp_find_target_def(root, fn_name, want_key)

    If target_def is not equal to 0:
        Note: The target definition is in this compilation's merged AST. Mangle from
        Note: the target's OWN stamped source_file (the authoritative, def-symmetric
        Note: derivation): the def label this same source_file produces downstream and
        Note: this call symbol are guaranteed identical.
        Let mangled_def be sepcomp_mangle_def(target_def, mangling_disabled)
        If want_key is not equal to 0:
            deallocate(want_key)
        End If
        If mangled_def is equal to 0:
            Note: Target resolves but opts out of mangling (main / no-source / unit
            Note: no-mangle) — keep the plain name and a plain call.
            Return 1
        End If
        call_expr_set_resolved_symbol(call_node, mangled_def)
        call_expr_set_cross_module(call_node, 1)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: No merged definition names this call. When the call is QUALIFIED `from
    Note: <Module>` and that alias maps to a known Import (want_key derived), the
    Note: target is a SEPARATELY-compiled module whose bodies were not spliced into
    Note: this unit; mangle straight from the import's module key exactly as the
    Note: monolith's lookup_qualified_target does. The separately-compiled module emits
    Note: the identical `<module_key>__<fn_name>` label, so the @PLT call resolves at
    Note: link time. Skip when this unit opts out of mangling.
    If want_key is not equal to 0:
        If mangling_disabled is equal to 0:
            Let mangled_import be sepcomp_mangle_with_key(want_key, fn_name)
            If mangled_import is not equal to 0:
                call_expr_set_resolved_symbol(call_node, mangled_import)
                call_expr_set_cross_module(call_node, 1)
            End If
        End If
        deallocate(want_key)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Unqualified bare call with no merged target: an External Process (libc /
    Note: runtime ABI symbol the linker resolves under its plain name) or a runtime
    Note: primitive reached without an Import. Leave it plain — the pre-existing
    Note: bare-call path emits `callq <name>` exactly as before this pass existed.
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Recursively walk an AST subtree, resolving every AST_CALL_EXPRESSION found.
Note: The walk descends through the children List (offset 24) of every node so call
Note: expressions nested anywhere in a function body (Return, Let, arguments, If/While
Note: bodies, nested calls) are all reached.
Process called "sepcomp_walk_resolve" takes root as Integer, node as Integer, mangling_disabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be ast_node_get_type(node)
    If kind is equal to DRIVER_AST_CALL_EXPRESSION:
        sepcomp_resolve_one_call(root, node, mangling_disabled)
    End If
    Let children be ast_node_get_children(node)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be list_length(children)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be list_get(children, i)
            If child is not equal to 0:
                sepcomp_walk_resolve(root, child, mangling_disabled)
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Entry point for the sep-comp AST mangle-resolve pass. Walks the merged program
Note: resolving every call site. Called from main after process_imports, before
Note: compile_program lowers the AST to HIR.
Process called "sepcomp_resolve_program" takes program as Integer returns Integer:
    If program is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mangling_disabled be sepcomp_mangling_disabled(program)
    sepcomp_walk_resolve(program, program, mangling_disabled)
    Return 0
End Process

Note: Main compiler entry point - Hybrid v0.0.8.5 Driver
Note: Uses v0.0.8.4.5 lexer/parser with v0.0.8.5 codegen primitives
Process called "main" takes argc as Integer, argv as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Supported command-line forms:
    Note:   runac <input.runa> <output.s>                 (argc == 3)
    Note:   runac <input.runa> <output.s> --target <key>  (argc == 5)
    Note: Any other argc is a usage error. The --target form publishes the
    Note: canonical platform key to the compile orchestrator's platform
    Note: constant-fold pass; without it the platform-dispatch ladders stay
    Note: intact and runtime selection takes over (legacy behavior preserved).
    Let has_target_flag be 0
    If argc is equal to 5:
        Set has_target_flag to 1
    End If
    If argc is not equal to 3:
        If has_target_flag is equal to 0:
            Let prog_name be get_command_line_arg(0)
            Let usage_msg_temp be string_concat("Usage: ", prog_name)
            Let usage_msg be string_concat(usage_msg_temp, " <input.runa> <output.s> [--target <key>]")
            deallocate(usage_msg_temp)
            Alert usage_msg
            deallocate(usage_msg)
            deallocate(prog_name)
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Get command line arguments (equivalent to input_filename = argv[1])
    Let input_filename be get_command_line_arg(1)
    Let output_filename be get_command_line_arg(2)

    Note: Resolve the optional --target <key>. When present (argc == 5) the third
    Note: arg must be exactly "--target" and the fourth must be one of the 18
    Note: canonical platform keys (validated via target_platform_index_for_key,
    Note: which returns 1..18 for a known key and 0 otherwise). The key string is
    Note: a get_command_line_arg result (freed only at process exit) so it
    Note: outlives the whole compile. Mirrors the monolith's --target handling.
    If has_target_flag is equal to 1:
        Let target_flag be get_command_line_arg(3)
        Let target_value be get_command_line_arg(4)
        If target_flag is equal to 0:
            Alert "[ERROR] Missing --target flag"
            deallocate(input_filename)
            deallocate(output_filename)
            Return 1
        End If
        If string_equals(target_flag, "--target") is equal to 0:
            Let bad_flag_msg be string_concat("[ERROR] Unrecognized option: ", target_flag)
            Alert bad_flag_msg
            deallocate(bad_flag_msg)
            deallocate(target_flag)
            deallocate(target_value)
            deallocate(input_filename)
            deallocate(output_filename)
            Return 1
        End If
        If target_value is equal to 0:
            Alert "[ERROR] --target requires a platform key argument"
            deallocate(target_flag)
            deallocate(input_filename)
            deallocate(output_filename)
            Return 1
        End If
        If target_platform_index_for_key(target_value) is equal to 0:
            Let bad_key_msg be string_concat("[ERROR] Unknown --target platform key: ", target_value)
            Alert bad_key_msg
            deallocate(bad_key_msg)
            deallocate(target_flag)
            deallocate(target_value)
            deallocate(input_filename)
            deallocate(output_filename)
            Return 1
        End If
        deallocate(target_flag)
        Note: Publish the validated key to the orchestrator's fold pass.
        set_active_target_platform_key(target_value)
        Note: Publish the same key to the import-closure platform-leaf skip gate so
        Note: only the target platform's primitives/platform/<key>/ leaves are merged
        Note: (the other 17 platforms' colliding bare globals are excluded entirely).
        set_driver_target_platform_key(target_value)
    End If

    Note: Read source file (equivalent to char *source = read_file(input_filename))
    Let source be read_file_internal(input_filename)

    Note: Check if reading failed (equivalent to !source)
    If source is equal to 0:
        Alert "[ERROR] Failed to read source file"
        deallocate(input_filename)
        deallocate(output_filename)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Modular frontend pipeline (v0.0.8.5). The lexer/parser are now the
    Note: split lexical/* and parsing/* subsystems whose API is:
    Note:   token_stream = quick_tokenize_string(source, source_length)
    Note:   parser       = parser_create(token_stream, arena)   (NOT parser_create(lexer))
    Note:   program      = parser_parse_program(parser)
    Note: The legacy one-argument parser_create(lexer) form no longer exists; the
    Note: parser consumes a token stream and needs a parse arena for temporaries.
    Let source_length be string_length(source)
    Let token_stream be quick_tokenize_string(source, source_length)

    Note: Check if tokenization failed
    If token_stream is equal to 0:
        Alert "[ERROR] main: Tokenization failed - token stream is NULL"
        deallocate(source)
        deallocate(input_filename)
        deallocate(output_filename)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Create parser over the token stream with a parse arena
    Let parse_arena be arena_create(65536)
    Let parser be parser_create(token_stream, parse_arena)

    Note: Parse program (Program *program = parser_parse_program(parser))
    Let program be parser_parse_program(parser)

    Note: Check if parsing failed (equivalent to !program)
    If program is equal to 0:
        Alert "[ERROR] main: Parsing failed - program is NULL"
        Note: Cleanup parser before returning
        parser_destroy(parser)
        deallocate(source)
        deallocate(input_filename)
        deallocate(output_filename)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Process imports: load and merge imported files. input_filename (argv[1])
    Note: is passed so process_imports can seed the root's own path into visited and
    Note: skip a cyclic import back to the root (prevents self re-merge / dup defs).
    Let import_result be process_imports(program, input_filename)
    If import_result is not equal to 0:
        Note: Import processing failed
        program_destroy(program)
        parser_destroy(parser)
        deallocate(source)
        deallocate(input_filename)
        deallocate(output_filename)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Sep-comp stages 3c+4: resolve every call site against the merged AST,
    Note: stamping each cross-object call with its module-mangled symbol + @PLT flag.
    Note: Runs after the import merge (so the full function table is present) and
    Note: before compile_program lowers AST->HIR (the carrier chain that threads the
    Note: results down to emit_call begins at HIR lowering). The def-label mangling is
    Note: driven separately by each definition's stamped source_file flowing through
    Note: HIR->MIR->LIR; the two derivations use the identical module_key_from_path so
    Note: caller symbol and callee label always agree.
    sepcomp_resolve_program(program)

    Note: Compile program using v0.0.8.5 primitives
    Note: Using v0.0.8.5 orchestration function
    Let compile_result be compile_program(program, output_filename)

    Note: Check if compilation failed
    If compile_result is not equal to 0:
        Note: Cleanup resources before returning
        program_destroy(program)
        parser_destroy(parser)
        deallocate(source)
        deallocate(input_filename)
        deallocate(output_filename)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Display success message (equivalent to printf("Successfully compiled '%s' to '%s'\n", input_filename, output_filename))
    Let success_msg_temp be string_concat("Successfully compiled '", input_filename)
    Let success_msg_temp2 be string_concat(success_msg_temp, "' to '")
    deallocate(success_msg_temp)
    Let success_msg be string_concat(success_msg_temp2, output_filename)
    deallocate(success_msg_temp2)
    Let success_msg_final be string_concat(success_msg, "'")
    deallocate(success_msg)
    Display success_msg_final
    deallocate(success_msg_final)
    program_destroy(program)
    parser_destroy(parser)
    deallocate(source)
    deallocate(input_filename)
    deallocate(output_filename)

    Return 0
End Process
